    "solution": "<p>For an alkane, the general formula is</p>\n<p>$$ C_nH_{2n+2} $$</p>\n<p>The combustion reaction of an alkane is</p>\n<p>$$ C_nH_{2n+2} + \\frac{3n+1}{2}O_2 \\rightarrow nCO_2 + (n+1)H_2O $$</p>\n<p>Given that 1 mole of the alkane requires 8 moles of oxygen, so</p>\n<p>$$ \\frac{3n+1}{2} = 8 $$</p>\n<p>Now solve:</p>\n<p>$$ 3n+1 = 16 $$</p>\n<p>$$ 3n = 15 $$</p>\n<p>$$ n = 5 $$</p>\n<p>So the alkane is</p>\n<p>$$ C_5H_{12} $$</p>\n<p>Now, total number of carbon and hydrogen atoms is</p>\n<p>$$ 5 + 12 = 17 $$</p>\n<p>So, the required answer is</p>\n<p>$$ \\boxed{17} $$</p>",
    "__v": 0,
    "title": "JEE Main 2026 (Online) 2nd April Morning Shift",
    "exam": "JEE Main"
  },
